        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 5:42PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 542 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Oil City, or near Sanford, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Midland around 605 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Laporte, Averill,
Porter Township, Gordonville, Poseyville, and North Bradley.

People attending Midland County Fair should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
